-- SPML Wins India Water Line Supply Contracts, Shares Climb
-- B y   K a r t h i k e y a n   S u n d a r a m
-- 2012-09-24T10:06:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-24/spml-wins-india-water-line-supply-contracts-shares-climb.html
SPML Infra Ltd. (SPML) , an Indian builder,
won 4.2 billion rupees ($78 million) of contracts for water
infrastructure work in the western state of Rajasthan. The
shares climbed to a three-month high.  The Kolkata company will commission, maintain and operate
the water supply projects being developed in the cities of
Pokharan, Balotra and Siwana for 10 years, according to a
statement filed to the stock exchange today.  SPML Infraâ€™s stock surged as much as 18 percent to the
highest since Aug. 17 in Mumbai trading. It traded at 73 rupees,
up 14 percent, as of 3:20 p.m local time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
